In Japanese, â€œmonoâ€ can be written using two different kanji: â€œç‰©â€ (for non-living things) and â€œè€…â€ (for a person). I think it was intended that way to make the meaning ambiguous (and I still think it is, in my opinion)â€”whether it refers to parental love as the â€œstrongest thing,â€ or to "the strongest person/s,â€ referring to the epic panel shown at the end of the chapter.
